
 INTRODUCTION :
같같같같같같같

Renoa wEditor is free software published under the GNU General Public License.
This editor provides Rich Text editing and supports multi-instances. You can see
an example at 'http://santx.free.fr/demo/wEditor/' by viewing source code.

Author(s)..: Vincent BATOUFFLET (FRANCE)
Contact....: santaurus@gmail.com


 HOW TO USE THIS EDITOR :
같같같같같같같같같같같같

In order to use this editor, you just have to add some lines in your current
HTML code.

1. LOAD SCRIPT

Add new line to load all required scripts between <HEAD> and </HEAD> tags.

<script language="javascript" type="text/javascript" src="./wEditor.js">
</script>


2. CREATE HIDDEN FIELD

After that, to use this editor and recover Rich Text as POST or GET variables,
you must create an INPUT hidden fields and specify it name as second parameter
of instance creation.

<input type="hidden" id="html_field" name="html_field" value="" />

--NOTE--------------------------------------------------------------------------
 This hidden field MUST be declared before a new instance creation.
 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 If 'value' attribute is specified, it will be used as default text.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


3. NEW INSTANCE

Create an instance of Renoa wEditor between <BODY> and </BODY> tags.

<script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
var your_instance = new wEditor("your_instance", "html_field");
your_instance.create();
</script>

--NOTE--------------------------------------------------------------------------
 If this editor have a container with CSS 'float' attribute, this won't work
 properly under Gecko 1.7.x engines based browsers (but works under 1.8b2).
 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 You must specify the same name for the variable and the instance name,
 otherwise this editor won't be able to work properly.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


4. ADD ONSUBMIT EVENT TO THE FORM

To get and transmit RichText generated by the editor like a GET or POST
variable, you must execute the 'validatePost' function at form submition.

<form [...] onsubmit="validatePost();">


5. ABSOLUTE URI

Set editorAbsoluteUri variable into 'wEditor.js' with the absolute URI (full
path, where the editor is stored in your website).
